deck_excerpt: Sucking accompanied with some Blue Eyes
deck_description: I honestly don't know why I made this deck. This deck isn't exactly perfect, so you can mess with the ratios if you want. It's a godless combination of Relinquished and a small Blue-Eyes engine. It does things. You can use White Stone of Ancients to either ritual Relinquished off of the actual ritual spell, or synchro into Formula Synchron, which will give a Blue-Eyes in the end phase to make Leo with on your opponents turn. Relinquished Fusion is a quick play, so you can summon Thousand-Eyes during the battle phase to save you a turn. Chaos MAX is in there because as long as I have Advance ritual art and Blue-Eyes, why not. Honestly this deck can do some cool things, but can brick harder than my jumpshot. Try it out if you want to have some fun.

deck_excerpt: This deck is one I tested and did well with, so I wanted to share it with you guys!
deck_description:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-MdBVIOWl3s&t=215s This deck doesn't really care about if it goes first or second, but it likes it's negate budget. Here is a good combo:
  1. Activate Allure to draw 2, then banish random DARK monster from your hand
  2. Normal Savant Kelper and activate his effect to add Dark Contract with the Gate
  3. Activate Gate to add Copernicus
  4. Activate random D/D/D monster in pendulum zone (perferably Abyss King Ragnarok)
  5. Use Swirl Slime to make Genghis
  6. Activate Swirl from grave to summon Copernicus
  7. Activate and Chain both Copernicus and Genghis to special Lamia from grave and then send necro slime to grave
  8. Synchro into Alexander using Genghis and Lamia
  9. Activate Ragnarok effect to bring Genghis back for 1000 LP
  10. Bring Lamia back with Alexander's effect
  11. link off Kelper and Copernicus into Cross-Sheep
  12. synchro into Meteorbusrt using Genghis and Lamia and special Ragnarok from pendulum zone
  13. Ragnarok effect to special Genghis from grave to a zone Cross-Sheep points to in order to activate effect to special Lamia back
  14. link Cross-Sheep and Lamia into Needlefiber (I refuse the english name) and special yet another Lamia from deck
  15. synchro Meteorburst and Lamia into Crystal Wing
  16. Use Lamia's own effect to pop Contract for it's return yet again
  17. synchro Alexander and Lamia into Savage and equip Cross-Sheep to it
  18. Necro Slime effect to banish itself and Alexander to fusion into your second Genghis
  19. Use Genghis and Ragnarok to XYZ into Hope Harvinger
  20. Prey your opponent can't break the epic board

deck_excerpt: Crystron Halqifibrax, Union Carrier, and Artifact Dagda from Duel Overload are all cards zombies can easily make and abuse for card advantage and cont
deck_description: Since the new Forbidden and Limited list hit all the OP extenders typically used in a combo zombie deck (Dangers, Glow Up Bulb, D. Hero Malicious, Destrudo, etc.,) I have been experimenting with using more cards from the zombie archetype. Since the deck has two natural targets for Cyrstron Halqifibrax's effect to summon a level 3 or lower tuner to your field in the form of Glow-Up Bloom and Uni-Zombie the number of brick-hands has been practically eliminated. The ideal going-first board can be achieved with a relatively consistent 3 combo;  Drawing a play starter (Shiranui Solitaire, Uni-Zombie, or Gozuki,) discard fodder (Necroworld Banshee, or Mezuki,) and any other extender/ free summon (Jack-o-Bolan, Danger! Mothman!, etc.) With a variation of these 3 cards alone it is possible to achieve an end-board of Zombie World, Doomking Balerdroch/Jack-o-Bolan (whichever you want to make off of Glow-Up Bloom,) Artifact Dagda, Artifact Scythe in the spell/trap zone and a Crystron Halqifibrax. During your opponent's main-phase you can activate Halqifibrax to summon T.G. Wonder Magician and destroy the set Artifact Scythe, triggering its effect to summon and lock your opponent out of their extra deck. Whenever your opponent summons or activates a card you can use Wonder Magician's effect to synchro summon with Scythe and make Shiranui Sunsaga, allowing an additional disruption in the form of destroying an opponent's card by shuffling back the Wonder Magician (not to mention at any time during all this you can chain to a monster effect to banish a monster from the field or grave, or negate a monster effect with Balerdroch.) If you would like me to make a combo tutorial video or to show some replays please like this deck profile or comment down below! Thank you!

deck_excerpt: Target-dodging Weather Painters that can bounce your opponent's everything and pump out The Weather Painter Rainbow in a matter of turns, resulting in
deck_description: The main strategy of the deck is to dodge targeting effects through the banish-return feature of the Painters, alongside your opponent not being able to touch your backrow due to Aurora's protection effect. The deck's main offensive feature is the bouncing of threats with The Weather Thundery Canvas, which can lead to your opponent's boards being made completely obsolete. Another useful feature of the deck is that it is difficult for your opponent to prevent the activations of your spells and traps because usually you won't be activating them, you will insteaed be "placing" them directly from your deck which doesn't count as an activation, thankfully. You also have access to The Weather Painter Sun, which can be used to make The Weather Painter Rainbow and then make its negation clause live almost immediately. Allowing you quick access to what is, in essence, three omni-negates and a copy of Solemn Warning with 2400 attack points. Also in the deck you have access to both Borreload and Borrelsword, which can both lead to quick OTKs with their high attack points and steal effect. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nRSTjoKGBA4

deck_excerpt: Full strategy listed. Really devastating buster blader deck. comment what you think. And enjoy.
deck_description:
okay so the strategy is pretty straight forward, the goal is to have a finish board of Buster dragon, Dragon destroyer and Vortex for negate.
easiest way to get there is:

either normal summon or special summon (using its effect) Darkwurm to bring Gate zero to your hand. ( if you use darkwurm as a discard for pendulum call, it’s an easy plus 2; bringing harmonizing and white wing to your hand).

If you still have a normal summon summon a level 4 or lower dragon monster. Buster welp’s effect adds destruction fusion to your hand. But if it dracoslayer that’s fine too. Link summon into Romulus, adding dragon ravine to your hand. Discard a card a send tempest to your graveyard (unless it break your scale)

use gate zero and any 8 scale apart from harmonizing magician for your pendulum scale. (harmonizing is to valuable when pendulum summoned but if it has to be done it has to be). Pendulum summon the harmonizing, darkwurm from your extra deck and dracoslayer if you have it, white wing magician if you have it and leave a zone open.

Upon pendulum summoning harmonizing special summon dragoncaller from you deck. And sychro summon Star eater. (Due to dragoncaller a effect if it attacks a dragon monster then it’s attack becomes 6400).

link summon Elpy and pisty using darkwurm and other level 4 or lower dragon monster. Special summon another darkwurm from your deck. Sychro Summon Buster dragon in defense using white wing and darkwurm. (This turns all opponents monster to dragons). Then special summon another dragon from your grave yard using pisty.

link summon skull dread using pisty, Elpy, Romulus and dragon to break guardragon lock. Drawing 4 cards, if you don’t already have destruction fusion in your hand then hopefully you draw it. If not add level 7 monster. (If you have another card in your hand so you can have a level 7 and destruction fusion then that’s the best) skull dreads effect to special summon level 7 and activate tempest effect banishing Elpy and pisty to special summon itself. Xyz summon odd-eyes absolute then link summon into galaxy satellite using absolute and skull dread. Which special summons odd-eyes vortex.
attack if you feel like.

if galaxy satellite is still on the field at the end of your opponents turn put buster blader or destruction fusion on top of your deck.

next turn is simple fusion summon dragon destroyer. Attack. ( if you are not going to end the duel by attack or it’s negated don’t worry) in main phase 2 pendulum summon any monster and link into protector welp, if you did not attack with dragon destroyer upon ending your turn protector welp then does damage to your opponent equal to dragon destroyers attack (which if there’s dragons on the field or graveyard then that’s quite a lot).

but that’s it, get your game on and high five the sky.

deck_name: Apex Avian turbo- post mr5 banlist
deck_excerpt: This is a deck with the main purpose of spitting out a full Apex Avian and Mist Valley Thunder bird infinite negate combo, along with a Cyber Dragon I
deck_description: summon two raid raptors (preferably lvl 4), make force strix, search either a black wing card or a singing lanius if you don't have one in hand, then summon wise strix. Using the free summon from deck due to link summon, summon a copy of zephyros if it is still in your deck (if it is in your hand don't fret summon a different blackwing), after that you go into a second force strix search, set soul shave force; activate it to summon a Cyber Dragon infinity. After summoning all of the blackwings you can use both raid raptor extra deck cards and go into the simorgh link, and a union carrier with the extra blackwings, then use union carrier to attach thunder bird from deck, attach union carrier to cyber dragon infinity using it's effect; and end turn, during the end phase summon Apex Avian. And remember to send the mist valley thunder bird as cost to the hand and not Apex Avian.

So, this is my first deck uploaded here.

This deck is unfortunetly not a budget option (rip destrudo), in this deck I play more Rokkets than other monsters.

Like in most decks You must play a few bricks.

Galactic Spiral Dragon is not a brick here but a "free cost",

You can discard him for Dragon Ravine, Twin Twister or Quadborrel and then return him from the gy to the field to make Harbinger.

 

Basic combo start for Dummies:

1. Summon any Rokket or best case scenario Seyfert.

1.1. Special summon if You are able Absorouter.

1.2. If you summoned Sefert you go "one card combo".

1.2.1. Tribute Seyfert for Collapserpent -> banish Seyfert -> Link Collapserpent into Striker -> add Boot Sector -> special Wyverbuster -> etc.

1.1.2 Link monster into Striker -> add Boot Sector -> link Absorouter and Striker into Romulus -> chain1-Romulus chain2-Absorouter -> etc.

2. At the end You usually have board with Spheres, Harbinger and Savage.

I could probably commit some grammar crimes, I'm not a native speaker.

Have fun and remember Dragon bullets for live~

deck_description:
you know the drill from the other 2 (which aged about as well as you'd think), use area 0 to search through the decks spell whilst clearing your own field with Redoer to use the effects of the striker cards you've probably searched via area 0 or Kagari.

The deck is relatively consistent and you will likely have a Redoer turn 1 at least though you can set up far more than that if the cards in your hand are good enough. the real issues for the deck mostly come in the form of towers monsters which the deck can really struggle to beat over outside of utopia double or in draguns case trying to bounce it with Redoer's trap effect. Other than that the deck has the same good/bad match ups as strikers and thief typically do with the exception of shaddoll which Redoer's effect will trigger when detached.

The 2 widow anchor is definitely nice to have back but the deck will need more to ever make a splash on the meta again besides new main deck stuff.

Use Imduk and World Legacy - "World Chalice" to link out Auram the World Chalice Blademaster, World Legacy - "World Chalice" will trigger its effect to ss lee, guardragon and add another guardragon to the hand. Use Auram to tribute lee and ss Imduk, link out Lib with a ball and Imduk, Imduk gonna trigger and ss guardragon,use Lib to set World legacy Succession. Use guardragon to link out Elpy, ss Omni, add World Legacy Guardragon Mardark. Ss Trishula by banishing 3 dragons and ban 3 cards. Ss Mardark, use Madark and Trishula to xyz summon True King of All Calamities. Ban guardragon, ss a normal mons. Use a ball, auram, venus and Lib to ss apollousa. Now u have 3 negates with apollousa, negate all mons effect on the field. Quite a strong field, doesn't it. deck_excerpt: My attempt at a Sacred Beasts Deck. Enjoy!
deck_description: This is my attempt at a Sacred Beasts deck. The goal is to get out your Sacred Beasts, and then eventually use them to Fusion Summon Armityle the Chaos Phantom, the deck's ace. You can use the various Continuous Spell/Trap cards in the deck to Summon Uria, Lord of Searing Flames, and Hamon, Lord of Striking Thunder. Use the Fiend monsters in the deck to Summon out Raviel, Lord of Phantasms. You can also use Sacred Beast support cards, like Hyper Blaze, Cerulean Sky Fire, or Phantasmal Martyrs to Summon them as well. And if one of your Sacred Beasts is destroyed, you can use Phantom of Chaos to replace it, or Dimension Fusion Destruction to Fusion Summon using your Graveyard. You can also use Chaos Core to get all three Sacred Beasts in your Graveyard right away to use Dimension Fusion Destruction, or use Summoning Beasts to Summon Sacred Beasts quickly. Then, you can use Fallen Paradise to use your Sacred Beasts to draw necessary from your Deck. You can also Fusion Summon Phantasm Emperor Trilojig, a mighty colossus on the battlefield. You can Synchro Summon Phantasmal Lord Ultimitl Bishbaalkin using Phantom King Hydride and Level Lifter. Card Guard can defend your cards, and Phantom Skyblaster can Summon Tokens to help you Summon out Raviel, Lord of Phantasms.

deck_name: Marik's dark army #1 Slifer and slime (40 card deck)
deck_excerpt: A deck based on Marik's deck he used when facing Yugi while controlling strings with some new cards and good strategy.
deck_description: This is a 40 card deck based on the deck Yami Marik used against Yugi, while controlling strings. Use cards like Nightmare's Steelcage and Gravity Bind to stop your opponents from attacking with there most powerful monsters. The get a revival jam on the field. You can activate Jam Defender and place some more monsters on the field, like Humanoid slime or Man-Eater Bug as a defense, and then you can summon and attack with Jinzo #7, who won't be effected by Gravity Bind, and can attack directly. By this time you might have Wave-Motion Cannon, and this can pretty much make you auto win if you've waited enough turns. After some more turns go by, you can use a combined effort of Wave-Motion Cannon and Gem flash (and also Jinzo#7) energy to deplete your opponents LP, and keep using Revival Jam as the ultimate defense, continuing to revive it! Of course, things might not always go this way, and we have XYZ's and Links, who don't have levels. You can easily destroy these monsters with Raigeki, plus you have other good spell and trap cards to foil your opponents plans as well, like Mystical Space Typhoon and Divine Wrath. If you don't have Raigeki, or it gets destroyed some how, you can use a better alternative to get rid of your opponents monsters: Lava Golem. Lava golem gets rid of two of your opponents monsters AND does 1000 damage to them turn after turn. And if you still have a Gravity Bind on the field, It won't be able to attack. If none of that works though, and you don't get lucky enough for the perfect strategy above, believe in the heart of the cards more! And try this next strategy. Using some new strategy, you can get Metal Reflect Slime on the field fairly easily, and with it protecting your LP get some more monsters on the field, protecting them with spells and traps. The easiest way to get quick monsters with this deck it to activate Jam Breeding Machine, summoning you some little jam tokens every turn. Now, once you have some Jams on your side, activate Mystical Space Typhoon, and get rid of your ow Spell: Jam Breeding Machine. With that card of the field, you can summon Slifer the Sky Dragon! If you don't have or have already used all your Mystical Space Typhoons, wait until your opponent destroys Jam Breeding Machine with one of there effects. People do that a lot when I duel them with this deck for some reason. Next use fusion sage if you've got it from the side deck, or use polymerization if you have it to fuse Slifer and Metal Reflect Slime to summon Egyptian God Slime! This card is practically unbeatable, not being able to be destroyed by battle, or targeted by card effects. This card can then destroy your opponent (with some help from the rest of your amazing deck) insuring victory. I know that you probs won't always be in the best position for one of these strategies, but there are many more inside the deck to explore. Have fun with this deck. It's surprisingly good. Btw in the extra deck a Fiber Jars, they are a banned card but if your playing for fun with no banned cards it's cool to have in the deck. (This is an updated version because my last didn't include polymerization.)

deck_name: GB with a dash of Tenyi
deck_excerpt: Gladiator beasts, supported by Tenyi, in a going second combo build to combat the meta - now including brief side deck discussions and budget choices!
deck_description:
Combo 1: rescue rabbit + gladiator beast's comeback/monster reborn
  • summon rescue rabbit & activate effect to special summon 2x GB andal
  • link 2x GB andal for test panther and activate effect to add gladiator beast attorix from deck to hand
  • use gladiator beast's comeback/monster reborn to special summon GB andal from GY
  • use test panther's second effect to shuffle back GB andal and special summon GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon GB attorix from hand
  • activate GB attorix effect to send GB augustus from deck to GY (or >5* GB from extra deck to GY)
  • contact fuse GB augustus & attorix to make GB tamer editor and activate effect to special summon GB Domitianus (negate 1 effect), GB heraklinos (negate spells/traps), or GB gyzarus (destroy 2 cards on field)
Proceed from combo 1 to combo 2 if you have an extender in hand (monster reborn, another GB comeback, or other method of special summon from GY) Combo 2:
  • link GB tamer editor & test panther for decode talker (or knightmare unicorn à apollousa if available)
  • special summon tamer editor from GY with extender
  • activate tamer editor effect again (soft once per turn) to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • note: special summon GB domitianus in combo 1, and heraklinos in combo 2 for 4+ negates when combined with decode talker
Combo 3: rescue rabbit + unexpected dai
  • activate unexpected dai to special summon GB andal from deck
  • normal summon rescue rabbit and activate effect to special summon 2 more GB andal from deck
  • link 2 GB andal (from rescue rabbit) for test panther
  • activate test panther effect to add GB attorix from deck to hand
  • activate second test panther effect to shuffle back GB andal and special summon GB augustus from the deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon GB attorix from hand
  • activate GB attorix effect to send GB augustus from deck to GY (or >5* GB from extra deck to GY)
  • contact fuse GB augustus & attorix for GB tamer editor & activate effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • proceed to combo 2 if you have an extender in hand
Combo 4 – Rejection Play: gladiator rejection + rescue rabbit
  • activate rejection, then normal summon rescue rabbit and activate effect to special summon 2x GB andal
  • chain rejection to special summon GB augustus from deck in DEF position
  • link one GB andal and GB augustus to make test panther
  • activate test panther effect to add GB darius from deck to hand
  • activate 2nd effect of test panther to shuffle GB andal back to deck and special summon second copy of GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon darius from hand
  • activate GB darius effect to special summon GB augustus from GY
  • contact fuse 2 GB augustus to make GB tamer editor
  • activate GB tamer editor effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • Options:
    1. link GB darius, GB tamer editor and test panther for apollousa
    2. link GB darius & test panther for decode talker
Combo 5 – Extended Rejection Play: gladiator rejection + rescue rabbit + unexpected dai/tenyi vishuda/tenyi adhara
  • activate rejection, then activate unexpected dai to special summon GB andal from deck (alternatively, special summon the tenyi monster)
  • chain rejection to special summon GB augustus from deck
  • normal summon rescue rabbit and activate effect to special summon 2 more GB andal from deck
  • link GB andal (from rescue rabbit) & GB augustus for test panther
  • activate test panther effect to add GB darius from deck to hand
  • activate test panther second effect to shuffle back GB andal (from rescue rabbit) and special summon GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon GB darius from hand
  • activate GB darius effect to special summon GB augustus from GY
  • contact fuse 2 GB augustus for GB tamer editor
  • activate tamer editor effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • Options without extender in hand:
    1. link test panther, GB tamer editor, and GB darius for borrelsword dragon/apollousa/zeroboros
    2. link test panther & GB tamer editor for decode talker, then overlay 4* GB monsters for rank 4 (e.g. abyss dweller, utopia OTK package etc)
  • Options with extender in hand:
    1. link test panther & GB tamer editor for decode talker, then overlay 4* GB monsters for rank 4 (e.g. abyss dweller), then activate extender to special summon GB tamer editor and activate effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus (5+ negates)
Combo 6 – Alt. Extended Rejection Play: gladiator rejection + unexpected dai + tenyi spirit monster
  • special summon tenyi spirit, then activate rejection
  • activate unexpected dai to special summon GB andal from deck, also chain rejection to special summon GB augustus from deck
  • link GB augustus & tenyi spirit for test panther and activate effect to add GB darius to hand
  • activate second test panther effect to shuffle back GB andal and special summon GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB august effect to special summon GB darius from hand
  • activate GB darius effect to special summon GB augustus from GY
  • contact fuse 2x GB augustus for GB tamer editor
  • activate GB tamer editor effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • Options with extender in hand:
    1. Proceed to combo 2
    2. Combo 8 (max negate) instead
  • Options without extender in hand:
    1. link test panther & GB tamer editor for decode talker
    2. link test panther, GB tamer editor, and GB darius for borrelsword dragon
Combo 7 – Naturia Beast: unexpected dai + rescue rabbit + tenyi spirit adhara + extender
  • essentially combo 1, but extra tenyi spirit adhara play
  • link test panther & GB tamer editor for decode talker
  • use extender to keep or revive adhara and 4* earth GB monster on board, synchro summon naturia beast at end of combo 1
Combo 8 - Max Negate: rescue rabbit + gladiator rejection + tenyi spirit adhara + comeback/monster reborn
  • special summon tenyi spirit adhara, then activate rejection
  • normal summon rescue rabbit and activate effect to special summon 2x GB andal from deck, also chain rejection to special summon GB augustus from deck
  • link GB andal & GB augustus for test panther and activate test panther effect to add Gb darius to hand
  • activate second test panther effect to shuffle back GB andal and special summon GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon GB darius from hand
  • activate GB darius effect to special summon GB augustus from grave (keep GB darius well away from link arrows)
  • contact fuse 2x GB augustus for GB tamer editor and activate effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • link GB tamer editor and test panther for decode talker
  • synchro summon naturia beast using GB darius and tenyi spirit adhara
  • activate GB comeback/monster reborn to special summon GB tamer editor from GY
  • activate GB tamer editor effect to special summon GB domitianus/heraklinos/gyzarus
  • Overall, 5+ negates and GB monsters cannot be targeted by opponent’s card effects outside of battle phase
Combo 9 – Unbricking a brick hand: 2x GB andal in-hand  /OR / unexpected dai + gladiator proving ground /OR/ GB andal + gladiator proving ground
  • summon GB andal by any method above and link away for link spider
  • activate link spider effect to special summon another GB andal from hand
  • link away GB andal & link spider for test panther and activate effect to add GB comeback from deck to hand (or GB attorix if already have an extender in hand)
  • activate GB comeback to special summon GB andal from GY
  • activate test panther's second effect to shuffle back GB andal and special summon GB augustus from deck
  • activate GB augustus effect to special summon GB attorix from hand
  • activate GB attorix effect to send GB augustus from deck to GY (or >5* GB from extra deck to GY)
  • contact fuse GB augustus & attorix to make GB tamer editor and activate effect to special summon GB Domitianus (negate 1 effect), GB heraklinos (negate spells/traps), or GB gyzarus (destroy 2 cards on field)
  • alternatively, if you do not have an extender in hand to begin combo; special summon GB darius instead of GB augustus and activate effect to special summon GB andal from GY, then overlay for rank 4 (e.g. abyss dweller, utopia OTK package etc)
  Notes:
  • Key goal – get a gladiator beast & non-gladiator beast monster on board (and ideally and extender in hand)
  • Whenever tenyi spirit vishuda is summoned, link it away for monk of the tenyi and use vishuda GY effect before continuing combos
  • Generally always want to summon GB domitianus first (protect against nibiru) and summon GB heraklinos second to protect against evely matched etc.
  • Can replace ash blossom with nibiru or mind control to increase combo potential in a go second strategy fully committed to board-breaking
  • Budget builds should replace 3x evenly matched with 1x rescue rabbit and 2x world legacy succession, and shift focus from a board-breaking go second strategy to a more balanced combo-centric strategy
  • Pot of desires may limit/dictate what combos you have access to, but the number of different combos as well as the consistency increase PoD provides outweighs the limitations
  • Apollousa not necessary for this build (though would be a good option) – decode talker has more utility with the going second aim of the deck to assist OTK potential whilst requiring one less link material
  • Vishuda & adhara have some level of recursiveness with each other if needed in the grind game

deck_excerpt: Turbo out some Seven Sins using Darklords, Dangers, and Dingirsu as the engine!
deck_description:
This deck is usually a deck that prefers to go second, as the main gameplan is to summon Condemned Darklord as quickly as possible if your opponent has a board with a lot of Monsters. If they don't negate anything, Normal Summon Darklord Morningstar using Condemned Darklord's effect and try to get some Level 8s (Superbia/Zerato) or Level 10s (2 Ixchels) to go into Xyz plays. If the opponent isn't immune to destruction effects, Xyz Summon Number 35: Ravenous Tarantula to get rid of all their monsters, otherwise, summon Dingirisu, use its effect, and then Rank Up into Number 77: The Seven Sins by summoning Number 84: Pain Gainer.

I picked Dangers! as a side engine for more draw power and the ability to get rid of certain cards in your hand, which Darklords can use in the GY. Bigfoot and Thunderbird were chosen specifically because they're Allure of Darkness and Trade-In targets and they can also pop cards if you need them to.

Monster Gate and Reasoning serve as potential millers for the deck, which can also lead into easy Special Summons. Be aware that any Nasten or Ixchel that you already Special Summoned this turn will just get milled if Monster Gate or Reasoning got it. Morningstar will always be milled because it can't be Special Summoned. For Reasoning, your opponent will most likely guess Level 8 if they know the Darklord matchup.

The most common way to turbo out a Morningstar is by using Ixchel and discarding another Darklord monster, drawing 2, and then using Darklord Contact to Special Summon Ixchel and then the other Darklord. Do this the other way around if you discard Superbia with Ixchel's effect. Link those 2 Darklords into Condemned Darklord, then use its effect (preferably discard a Darklord Trap or a Danger! Monster) and search for Morningstar. Use Morningstar's effect to swarm the board with huge Darklords and then go into your plays from there.

The main weaknesses to Darklords as an archetype are basically backrow removal and their dependence on Special Summoning and draw power. DROLL & LOCK BIRD IS REALLY ANNOYING FOR THIS DECK. Zombie World changes your gameplan of Summoning Morningstar because Condemned Darklord requires Fairy Monsters. This means Zombie World also makes Superbia's effect not work. Because the deck is mostly Dark-Attribute, that does mean your opponent can use Super Polymerization to summon Starving Venom Fusion Dragon, so be aware that they can disrupt your plays that way.

However, they are really good at non-targeting effects, as all of their Trap cards don't target and Dingirsu has non-targeting removal. They're also really great at summoning a bunch of high ATK/DEF monsters to the field if your opponent isn't the strongest against high ATK/DEF swarm.

For the side deck, I have 3 Twin Twisters for the backrow removal issue, 2 Darklord Tezcatlipoca if you need an extra Darklord with the Spell/Trap effect, 2 The Sanctified Darklord in case I need to search for effect negation or mill it with Ukoback, 2 Archlord Kristya for another Trade-In target and in case I need to lock my opponent out of Special Summoning, and 2 Michion, the Timelord for another Level 10 and for huge damage (Xyz into Gustav Max in MP2 to do even more).

Other side deck cards (these might change later on) are Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Juggernaut Liebe, Number 23: Lancelot, Dark Knight of the Underworld, Five-Headed Link Dragon (it does come up sometimes), and Topologic Bomber Dragon.

deck_excerpt: The cutest possible archetype. The beaver's cause I'm Canadian ;)
deck_description: Just building Merfae for casual fun, seeing how well the archetype might hold up. The deck does seem to get a fair number of interactions up on the opponent's turn, but struggles to actually close games. Then again, with Merfae Hide-and-Seek the deck has a really solid plan to win in the grind-game. I feel like the deck would struggle at the competitive level, largely because of the timer, but also because it's weak, and also highly skill-intensive to pilot, since your plays happen on your opponent's turn. You have to finish setting up while they're setting up, and then know when to do everything to get the most value and that also means understanding your opponent's deck. So if that sounds like your kind of game plan, you could probably pilot it to moderate success. They ARE cute AF tho, and stronger in practice than they look on paper.

deck_excerpt: This is my first deck which I made from scratch after playing dueling nexus for 2 months. It's basically a gamble, because most of your deck gets bani
deck_description: This is my first deck which I made from scratch after playing dueling nexus for 2 months. It's basically a gamble, because most of your deck gets banished by the 5th turn unless you got Necroface. Don't worry though, it's strong enough to destroy a tier 2 deck in less than 6 turns. Stats: Drawing Power: B Summoning Power: A Destructive Power: A  Defensive Power: B Flexibility: A+  Enjoyment: S Main Features: Summoning Engine: Danger! Archetype & Golden Castle Combos w/ Link, Xyz Drawing Engine: Danger! Archetype, Bamboo Swords, Trade-In, Allure of Darkness, & Pot of Desires Trap Type: Monster Traps, Crackdown Other Cool Features: Increase your life points with absurd amounts using Soul Absorption + Golden Castle + Pot of Desires + Gizmek Orochi Destroy their backrow with Twin Twisters & Galaxy Cyclone! Summon an indestructible Saryuja Skull Dread with I:P Masquerena + Knightmare Phoenix OTK your enemy with Topologic Zeroboros or Gren Maju Da Eiza! Surprise your annoying opponent with Witch's Strike! Troll your enemies with Time Thief Redoer ! Activate a graveyard Galaxy Cyclone on their Mystic Mine to surprise your opponent! Be persistent in summoning with Gizmek Orochi's effect! Destroy their indestructible monsters with Lava Golem + Gizmek Orochi (effect) ! Finish your enemy with Utopia the Lightning! How to Combo: Get a Golden  Castle using Glife, Terraforming, or Metaverse. Activate the Golden Castle then special summon Iron Hans. Use Iron Hans effect to summon Iron Knight. Link summon into Isolde, then activate first effect to get Black Luster Envoy. (if unavailable get armageddon knight) Activate second effect of Isolde, then sacrifice Cursed Bamboo and Broken Bamboo to summon hero kid. Summon 3 hero kids, then use cursed bamboo effect to pick which bamboo sword you need at the present moment. Link summon I:P Masquerena using 2 Hero Kids. If you don't have a "Danger!" card or Gizmek Orochi to special summon, use foolish burial on Orcust Knightmare or Gizmek Orochi. (Use your spell & traps) Special summon with a "Danger!" card in your hand or Gizmek Orochi. If you get 4 monsters with different names in your field, link summon Saryuja Skull Dread. Draw 4 cards, then put back hero kid, iron knight, iron hans, or other cards you don't need. Optional: (Use trade ins, allure of darkness, bamboo swords to draw more cards.) Activate saryuja's effect to summon any monsters you can't summon in your hand. Special summon any monsters you can summon. If you have 2 level 8 monsters in your field, xyz summon Number 38 under Saryuja. Optional: (Link summon knightmare phoenix directly under Saryuja using other monsters to make it immortal.) Defensive Tactics: Use Crackdown or Lava Golem on any supposedly unbeatable monster(s) your opponent have. Activate Ghost Ogre's effect when the enemy  summons a boss monster, don't use it immediately. Summon Necroface when you are running out of cards in your deck. When your opponent have too many trap cards, summon gren maju in face-down position to perform a thunder cross split attack. Replaceable Cards:  Trap cards w/ another traps Bamboo swords w/ another draw engine Danger! cards w/ another easy special summon engine Pseudo Statistics: 70% chance of getting golden castle in your first hand. 90% chance of beating any random deck. 65% chance of beating any tier 2 deck. 10% chance of getting non-usable cards at first hand. 99.99% chance of having fun. Strengths: Can beat a blue eyes deck 55% of the time. Can beat a hero deck 60% of the time. Can beat a psy-frame deck 70% of the time. Can play toe to toe with some other popular decks. Weaknesses: Loses to mystic mine users 55% of the time. Loses to monarchs or gladiators 70% of the time. Loses to subterror decks 90% of the time. Loses to the opponent  who uses boring archetypes that negates everything 99% of the time. (I'm looking at you herald of perfection.) That's all, I hope you have some fun. I know this deck is still imperfect oh well.

deck_name: ABC Danger Post April Master Rules.
deck_excerpt: ABC Danger, Post Master Rules April 2020
deck_description:
To keep this as short and sweet as possible, this deck is primarily built to OTK, but if it fails to to so setup so next tutn your opponent doesn't really have many options to react. ABC and Dangers have such amazing synergy it's shocking that it's been overlooked in favour of the Infinity build with the upcoming Union support. Given that almost every player anticipates the Infinity build being the main ABC build for the new format, this version often ends up being a deadly surprise. What surprised me most when testing this build was how flexible the extra deck is. The Dangers, Destrudo and Gizmek allow the opportunity to use so many cards for going both first and second that at times I've struggled to find a permanent setup. Once the meta defines itself, the extra can be tailored to be a lot more specific. The side deck is pretty general right now. Can easily be tailored to the format, but i'm pretty happy with it as an initial start.

deck_excerpt: Protection strategy with Mystic Mine that will help you summon the invincible Exodia!
deck_description:
The deck consists of searching as fast as possible for the Mystic Mine, which will help us to maintain ourselves and prevent the opponent's plays.

Once the Mine is activated, the next step will be to leave the support cards such as Dark Bribe (denier), Field Barrier (obviously, field protector), Threatening Roar (insurance in case the mine is destroyed) and Demise of the Land or Metaverse (so that if the mine is destroyed we can bring another one immediately). Obviously we cannot play all of them, we will have to be smart to know which ones should be left on the field; the optimum is 2 although as long as we have no more than 3 it will be fine although we can have complications with cards that need to stay on the field like Shard of Greed. To help us find the cards we need, we have a good variety of draw cards (be careful, you should not underestimate the draw power of the deck, I have mistakenly burned it all for activating cards without seeing how many cards were left in the deck).

Last and most importantly, the win conditions. Of course we have Exodia, the king of the Deck who with so many draw cards and our safeguard strategy will not be very difficult to get, and we have Final Countdown too that gives us an extra win condition (I do not recommend activating it without at least 25 cards remaining especially if they are in a tournament and there is little time left since we could lose for LP).

The Extra Deck can be anything since we will only use it to activate Pot of Extravagance although we can make a good security strategy with Linkuriboh, Almiraj and Gardna although we will have activated Final Countdown or have done side deck Dark Factory (or both) or practically we can give up (in any case I don't recommend summoning monsters since that could give our opponent the opportunity to purposely keep a single monster to destroy the Mine by its own effect in case we don't have Field Barrier, it's difficult but it is not about giving opportunities to our opponent).

Finally, the Side Deck does not need much explanation; Dark Factory in case our opponent has what to send the exodia pieces to the cemetery with, foolish burial is by itself only one piece was sent to the cemetery we can send another to activate the effect of Dark Factory, Cosmic Cyclone can help us to activate Hope for Escape and the rest of the cards you just have to be wise to know what to change, it is what will help us win.

NOTE: I know that Pot of Extravagance is very expensive so if you don't have it and you can't afford it I suggest Jar of Greed to replace it. Of course it is not the same but the strategy of activating 3 Reckless Greed at the same time will not be difficult and sending 10 cards from the deck to the cemetery with Pot of Desires is not a very good idea playing Exodia so I consider it the best option (I accept suggestions).

By last... Sorry for the G Translate English.

deck_excerpt: This Fur Hire Deck is made for a simple combo: to summon Folgo and OTK with Rafale and ESCHATOS!!!
deck_description:
This Fur Hire Deck is made for a simple combo: to summon Folgo and OTK with Rafale and ESCHATOS!!! Going 2nd is the best thing if you want to make a disaster, but if you go 1st you could block your opponent summoning both Rafale and Wiz, so you will have 2 negation. You could play cards as There Can Be Only One or some Solemn cards to block opponent's combos.

The main combo is:

Normal summon Beat, Special Summon another Fur Hire Monster with Beat's effect and search for Rafale (or another Fur Hire if you already have Rafale in your hand), Special summon Another Fur Hire Monster and special summon Rafale as the 4th monster triggering his effect and adding a card to your hand choosing between 3 cards (better a Fur Hire monster or Eschatos). Special summon Folgo using the three Fur Hire monsters on the field (do not use Rafale) and triggering his effect special summoning Wiz. Trigger wiz's effect and gain 1000LP. So, special summon Eschatos by banishing the 3 monster you used to link summon Folgo, active his effect to cleaning the oppenent's side of the field and triggering Folgo's effect to draw 3 cards! So you can attack with Folgo (2400), Rafale (2800) and Eschatos (3000) and win the mach!

If you go 1st you can stop at the summoning of Wiz, so you will have 1 monster's effect negation and 1 spell/trap's negation. If you set cards like Called By The Grave or Solemn Warning/Strike or There Can Be Only One to block other opponent's combos, you are quite sure to start your second turn without problems.

 

Other little tips:

If you want you can start with Reasoning. Your monsters are all of different levels and guessing the correct level will be very hard to your opponent. You can use Reasoning to restart the effects chain after a nagation too.

If your opponent negates one of your Fur Hire monster's effect, you can use Monster Gate to "switch" the Fur Hire monster on the field with another one and restart with the effects chain.

If you haven't enough monster to link summon Folgo, you can use One-Time Passcode to summon a cyberce-type Token and have a free material to summoning Folgo.

For the same problem, you can siding One For One and use it to sending a monster to the GY and special summon Filo from the deck, then special summon another monster from your hand and trigger Filo's effect to special summoning the monster you sent to the GY with the effect of One For One, thus having 3 monster for link summoning Folgo.

I suggest you summon Rafale under Folgo, so you can link summon Underclock Tacker on his right and active his effect to make one of your opponent's monster lose 2800 ATK and make easier to you to destroy that monster by battle.

the extra deck isn't very important: Borreload and Topologic Bomber are only supports 'cause you won't need them too much.

deck_excerpt: Engage is Banned? Let me introduce you Pot of Avarice.
deck_description:
Engage might be gone, but the engine is all there, and it allows you to go +1 every turn.

The main strategy is starting your Sky Striker plays going second, do the Hayate-Kagari play and end with Shizuku adding 2 cards on the process.

You need 3 Roze to draw them consistently. Hayate can send Raye to the GY and don't forget to use Roze's effect.

Ghost Belle and Called by the Grave are musts against hand traps because if your cards does not resolve you cannot control the board. (Keep in mind that Belle can negate Called so that your Raye will resolve)

This is basically the same thing we've been done during the last format, but now Pot of Avarice is unlimited, and in this deck you can basically call it Pot of Greed. Now you don't need to worry about using all of your Link monsters because your're going to take them back anyways. there's no need to run Hercules Base, whose equip effect was almost never used.

Foolish Burial goods is still alive and it helps you getting your widow anchor if forced to go first. Three copies of Area Zero will help you change brick spells for your engine cards and the field's second effect is more accessible with Zeke.

Please, don't run multiple copies random Striker cards like Jamming, Eagle, Vector, Scissors. I'm using 2 Cannon and 2 Afterburners because they are really useful, but there are no excuses for running Scissor or a Second Jamming Waves, keep in mind that if your Engine is disrupted you need defense and draw power, not a third Eagle Booster.

Sky Striker Ace - Zeke is the new Link monster, and that card's effects may not impress that much but it does so much for this deck. Now you can take you opponents monsters (shark and anchor) without fearing a field miss and link them off for another Sky Striker Ace monster ending the turn with your spells on full power. The Banish effect is really convenient because it helps you clearing the board, but also versatile once you can banish himself to always have a play or banish the monster you took with Shark Cannon, so that it can attack when it comes back. Not to mention that Zeke has a down arrow which helps you making Ningirsu.

The hand traps are really important because they can fulfill your graveyard with targets for Avarice and simplify the game state. Also you can normal summon them to link scale when needed.

Pankratops is a good body that can help you outing Imperial Order, link scaling and doing that extra damage Sky Strikers Need from time to time.

Of course this deck is not good going first, but it's one card engine allows you to side whatever cards you think will perform well on the format like TCBOO, but in this case i'm running Dimensional Barrier. Against Combo decks i'm running Sphere Mode and Dark Ruler no More, but if you don't want to give away your normal summon just use Nibiru instead.

On the overall Sky Striker might not be the most explosive deck available but you have a ton of in-theme disruptions and a lot of space for extra negates which makes it playable.

The deck could be even more powerful with Mystic Mine, but i don' like that card and i think you have to play the deck in a complete different way otherwise you will just be surprised when your opponent outs it and OTKs you :)

deck_excerpt: Just your regular Gouki deck but instead of Cyber-stein, we're playing Silent Swordsman for spell negation. Consistent link 4 (Giant Ogre, Apollousa,
deck_description: Basic strategy is to resolve many different Gouki monsters as much as possible (minimal 2 so our Gouki Rematch is online). From there you can go for any link play while searching tons of card, my preferred end board is Apollousa + Linkuriboh/Silent Swordsman. Also dont forget to search God Phoenix Gearfried via Isolde. Going second is much easier as we can OTK with Giant Ogre or Accescode to break board + big damage (you can link climb it from Unicorn for maximum atk gain and more removal). Expected end board: Pros: Very consistent, every Gouki monster replaces itself, great follow up play, great going first or second, bunch of handtraps, many possible big beater monsters (some with non-targeting removal). Cons: First turn board isnt too strong, bad matchup against backrow deck, possible bricking with the Silent Swordsmen and handtraps.

deck_excerpt: Steal Your Opponent's Monsters and Use them as Material For Your Own Summons!
deck_description:
Tatsunecro + Mezuki = Summon Tatsunectro and synchro with the 2 for Red-Eyes Zombie Necro Dragon then use Mexuki to get Tatsuneco back for Sunsaga

Zombie World + Super Poly = Summon Dragonecro with your opponent's monsters!

Necroworld Banshee is good graveyard fodder and can be sent by Zombie Master, Tributed for Red-Eyes Zombie Dragon, or Used for Synchro. (Preferably with Tatsunecro)

Banshee + Tatsunecro = Synchro with Tatsunecro for Ancient Pixie Dragon, then banish Banshee for Zombie World.

Plaguespreader Zombie + any lv 4 = Synchro for a lv 6 then use Plaguespreader's Effect and Synchro again for Beelze (if the other material was Mezuki you can summon Plaguespread again for Sunsaga)

Zombie World can be searched with Banshee, Terraforming, or Metaverse and should be done so quickly because the effects of cards like Doomking Balerdrach, Doomkaiser Dragon, and the 2 Red-Eyes depend on it, while it also supports Super Poly, Return of the Zombies, and Zombie Master.
